ENTRY       EC 1.8.2.3                  Enzyme
NAME        sulfide-cytochrome-c reductase (flavocytochrome c)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on a sulfur group of donors;
            With a cytochrome as acceptor
SYSNAME     hydrogen-sulfide:flavocytochrome c oxidoreductase
REACTION    hydrogen sulfide + 2 ferricytochrome c = sulfur + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 H+ [RN:R09499]
ALL_REAC    R09499
SUBSTRATE   hydrogen sulfide [CPD:C00283];
            ferricytochrome c [CPD:C00125]
PRODUCT     sulfur [CPD:C00087];
            ferrocytochrome c [CPD:C00126];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme from Allochromatium vinosum contains covalently bound FAD and covalently-bound c-type hemes.
